google-research/google-research.msg:
- bug fixes in random.py on choosing group size for Mezard selector with variable sens/spec;
- minor naming change of parameter in SmcSampler class;
- if @LbpSampler() is not instantiated in gin file as a cheap_sampler, gin bindings are ignored, hence added to the default .gin config;
- transitioned from a fixed number of iterations to a more detailed parameterization for LBPs execution. Now comes with min/max iterations and target tolerance on two successive iterations;

- when the difference between successive iterations does not go below this tolerance  within max_iterations, and the difference is substantial, LBP is likely cycling. This triggers now a SMC sampler to compute the marginal at the level of simulator.py

- For some selectors, keeping track of which groups were tested positive and need to be subsequently cleared is important (e.g. Dorfman methods). When mixing Dorfman with non-adaptive methods this can be a problem, now added a flag to handle this situation

- Informative Dorfman has now a flag that selects the "modified" behavior we had introduced in the paper. This is in order to study the original algorithm, not only our version that was taking random subsets. User can therefore use standard ID or our modified ID which can take num_tests_per_cycle into account.

