tensorflow/adanet.msg:
Fix Travis CI build to run all tests.

Passing build: https://travis-ci.org/tensorflow/adanet/builds/455559474

Halved test runtime from 7m59s to 4m54s on local Linux machine by switching test `Heads` to `regression_head` from `binary_classification_head` and lowering learning rate. Halving the total runtime allows Travis to finish running all tests in ~35 minutes, whereas before `//adanet/core:estimator_test` would timeout after an hour. It would appear that computing sigmoids is much more expensive on commodity CPUs.

